<div>
    <h1>How to View Training Report in Phishsims</h1>

    <h2>Dashboard View</h2>
    <h6>1. Accessing the Dashboard</h6>
    <ol>
        <li>Log in to your Phishsims account.</li>
        <li>Navigate to the Dashboard section.</li>
        <img src="/img/Template1.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
    </ol>

    <h6>2. Monthly Training Reports</h6>
    <ol>
        <li>Within the "Report Tabs" section on the Dashboard, locate the Monthly Training Reports.</li>
        <li>These reports provide insights into training progress on a month-to-month basis.</li>
        <img src="/img/Template10.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
    </ol>

    <h6>3. Bar Chart Overview</h6>
    <ol>
        <p>The Training Report is presented through an interactive bar chart.</p>
        <p><strong>Training Metrics:</strong></p>
        <p>1. Training Assigned: Number of recipients who received training assignments after being phished.</p>
        <p>2. Training Completed: Recipients who successfully completed their training.</p>
        <p>3. Training In Process: Recipients who are in the process of completing their training.</p>

    </ol>

    <h6>3. Interacting with Charts</h6>
    <ol>
        <p>Clicking on any bar within the chart provides a detailed list of recipients associated with that specific training status (assigned, completed, in process).</p>
        <p>The list includes recipients who have not yet started their training, providing a comprehensive view of training progress.</p>



    </ol>



    <h2>Training Page View</h2>

    <h6>1. Accessing the Training Page</h6>

    <ol>
        <p>From the main navigation menu, select the "Training" option.</p>
    </ol>

    <h6>2. Detailed Training Reports</h6>
    <ol>
        <p>The Training Page offers a detailed view of training activities and progress.</p>
        <p><strong>Metrics include:</strong></p>
        <li>Recipients who received training assignments..</li>
        <li>Recipients who completed their training.</li>
        <li>Recipients who are currently in the process of completing their training.</li>
        <li>Recipients who have not started their training.</li>

    </ol>
    <h6>3. Individual Training Status</h6>
    <ol>
        <p>Each recipient's training status is clearly indicated, including completion percentage for those in progress.</p>
        <p>The report provides insights into individual training engagement and progress.</p>

     

    </ol>

    <h6>4. Interacting with Reports</h6>
    <ol>
        <p>You can interact with the Training Report on the Training Page by accessing individual recipient details.</p>
        <p>Detailed information includes recipient ID, training status, completion percentage, and training assignment details.</p>


    </ol>


    <h2>Conclusion</h2>
    <p>By following these steps, you can effectively view Training Reports in Phishsims from both the Dashboard and the dedicated Training Page. The interactive bar charts on the Dashboard offer a quick overview of monthly training metrics, while the Training Page provides detailed insights into individual recipient training statuses and progress. This information is crucial for evaluating training effectiveness and ensuring comprehensive cybersecurity awareness across your organization.

</p>

